#          LonStackTest.scr
#          v1.0.0
#
# Title:   LON Stack NodeUtil Test Script
#
# Purpose: Test basic LON Stack functionality using NodeUtil on a laptop
#          with U10 LON USB interface and a test device with a LON stack
#          test application, and a U60 Rev C LON USB interface.  The test
#          script concludes with a NodeUtil performance test that sends
#          1000 acknowledged messages to the test device.
#
# Notes:   This script assumes the test application sends at least one
#          Service Pin message on startup and implements the network variables
#          implemented by the LonStackExample1 application included with 
#          LON Stack DX.
#
#          To run this script:
#          1. Start NodeUtil; for example: nodeutil -dlon1
#          2. Start the test device application which should send at least one
#             Service Pin message
#          3. Start this script with: (<) LonStackTest.scr
#
#          The test script creates a LonStackTest.log file that contains the
#          NodeUtil output generated by the sript.

# List devices
L
# Send Service Pin message
P
# Go to device 1
G
1
# Report test device status and statistics
S
N
# Change test device mode to offline
M
F
# Report test device status and statistics
S
N
# Change test device mode to online
M
N
# Report test device status and statistics
S
N
